=C2=A0

It=E2=80=99s certainly a relationship that=E2=80=99s developing. I think Th=
une has done so many of the right things to further it and speed it along. =
It=E2=80=99s a new relationship, but it
can=E2=80=99t be worse than the previous one. Anyone walking through that d=
oor will be a breath of fresh air compared to who was in place before.

=C2=A0

How long do you think it will take to pass this legislation=E2=80=94tax cut=
s, immigration, energy, etcetera? This is a massive bill. Where do you thin=
k there are going to be reservations?

=C2=A0

I know House Republicans are unhappy about pieces of it that they feel are =
inconsistent with what we just ran on and won on, like some of the giveaway=
s that they think are things that were promised to Democrats. But that=E2=
=80=99s where the slim majority comes in. Then you have Christmas and the h=
olidays, and you=E2=80=99ve got January 20 coming up around the corner pret=
ty fast. At the same time, Trump=E2=80=99s focused on the cabinet and getti=
ng his people in place and assembling a government. So
there are a ton of competing interests when it comes to time. How long one =
or two bills takes=E2=80=94your guess is as good as mine. There are a lot o=
f balls in the air that make things complicated.

=C2=A0

They=E2=80=99re almost certainly going to lose the House; history tells us =
that, especially with a slim majority. So you=E2=80=99ve got one term in fr=
ont of you, and you=E2=80=99ve got two years before you probably lose contr=
ol of the House. That=E2=80=99s why he=E2=80=99s
been so aggressive in trying to get his people in place in the cabinet, bec=
ause he understands that, unlike 2017, when he was walking in the door with=
 potentially eight years in front of him, he=E2=80=99s got 18 months. It=E2=
=80=99s a much different clock. He understands the timeline, and there=E2=
=80=99s a quickened pace with everything he=E2=80=99s doing this time aroun=
