The =E2=80=9CShow of Strength=E2=80=9D Theory
---------------------------------

What was Trump=E2=80=99s relationship with pollsters when you were
with him in the White House?

=C2=A0

He liked pollsters when their numbers were good, and he didn=E2=80=99t like=
 them when they were bad. He looked at polls, but he was far from obsessed =
with them. He paid attention when you had something to show him, but he was=
 guided more by his instinct than he was by a pollster=E2=80=99s number tha=
t was published somewhere. He used polls to verify his instincts, but they =
weren=E2=80=99t
guiding his agenda or thought process.

=C2=A0

One of Trump=E2=80=99s greatest strengths is messaging. In his first term, =
he fired off a flurry of executive orders that were pretty much toothless a=
nd couldn=E2=80=99t be upheld in court. How much of this is Trump=E2=80=99s=
 way of sending a message to the American people that he=E2=80=99s trying t=
o make good on his promise, and if it fails, it=E2=80=99s not because of hi=
m?

=C2=A0

From my perspective, those are less legislative documents than they are gui=
ding principles and shows of strength. They=E2=80=99re more, I=E2=80=99m do=
ing on Day One what I promised to do and what you elected me to do. Most Am=
ericans don=E2=80=99t know what the hell an executive order is, or if somet=
hing is subsequently held up in the courts, or overturned. They see him sit=
ting at his desk with a big pen and a document with his
big signature on the piece of paper. And it=E2=80=99s the picture and messa=
ging that matters a whole lot more than what happens after. Candidly, peopl=
e are going to pay attention to what pictures they see on Day One.

=C2=A0

Do you think Trump is genuinely eager to expand the power of the executive =
branch?

=C2=A0

I don=E2=80=99t know the answer to
your question. I would say the thing he can do most to have expansive power=
s is continue to do what he=E2=80=99s doing right now. Right now, he=E2=80=
=99s so much stronger than he was eight years ago, when Americans gave him =
even marks and his approval rating was plus-one. Now, it=E2=80=99s approach=
ing plus-20. You can do a whole lot more with the bully pulpit when you=E2=
=80=99re strong politically. The best way to expand your powers is to look =
